reviews.review_text:
hot for '79 Glad this is hear at least because I hear the best playing of '79 (along with the Nassau shows). It's one of those nights where things are falling into place for Mr. G.
I'll be checking back for the death copy.

bread crumb Although you can't hear it here, this is Brent's first Cold Rain and Snow.  A tune that I think this incrantion of the band really tore up.  Jerry's intonation of the lyrics varies from a plea to a snarl and it always seems to work.  Ship of Fools, also found here, is kind of the same thing - sometimes we're begged and sometimes we're commanded, but we always heed the advice.
My first show... Did't know what to expect but loved it.
